        "**9. Refrigeration System Performance Calculations**\n",
        "\n",
        "We use the P-h diagram approach with R134a refrigerant properties.\n",
        "\n",
        "From R134a saturation tables:\n",
        "\n",
        "At low pressure (0.3 MPa) → evaporator temperature ≈ 0.6°C\n",
        "\n",
        "At high pressure (1.8 MPa) → condenser temperature ≈ 57.9°C"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DoBNOb4UebC2"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ── R134a ENTHALPY VALUES (from standard P-h / refrigerant tables) ─────────────\n",
        "# State points on the P-h diagram:\n",
        "#   h1 = enthalpy after evaporator  (saturated vapour at low pressure)\n",
        "#   h2 = enthalpy after compressor  (superheated vapour at high pressure)\n",
        "#   h3 = enthalpy after condenser   (saturated liquid at high pressure)\n",
        "#   h4 = enthalpy after expansion   (h4 = h3, throttling process)\n",
        "\n",
        "# R134a property values at measured pressures (kJ/kg)\n",
        "h1 = 398.6    # kJ/kg  – saturated vapour at 0.3 MPa (evaporator exit)\n",
        "h2 = 435.0    # kJ/kg  – superheated vapour at 1.8 MPa (compressor exit)\n",
